what is the diff b/w cetralized and distributed control system?
In centralized vesrision control system (CVCS) there is only one central server that store the code. Developers 
need to connect to the server to get the latest code and save changes.
In Distribited version control system (DVCS) every developer has a complete copy of the repository on their local 
machine. They can work and commit changes even without internet access.

