What are pre-commit hooks and post-commit hooks?
A pre-commit hook runs before a commit and used to validate code or run checks.
Purpose:- Check code quality, Run tests, Validating formatting and prevent bad commit's

A post-commit hook runs after a successful commit and is used to send notifications, update logs and trigger other 
automation tasks

What is branch?
A branch is an independent line of development in Git that allows us to work on changes without impacting the
main branch until the changes are tested and merged.

